		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">[5], the committee may decide [6] to use the work of professional artists or to hold a competition and ask the public to enter their own artwork. [7] professionals are to be used, three artists will normally [8] to submit designs. The best of these will [9]. Prior to printing, however, the design must be endorsed by the Secretary for Home Affairs. If, on the other hand, the committee decides to use amateur artwork, then a competition will be set up and publicised. [10] entries have been submitted, the committee will [11] the best and the winning artwork is [12] for printing.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
